blog.name: autonomy1
blog.title: Peter Percival-AUTONOMY
blog.description: Shades, nuances, scraps of existence......looking directly at an object can sometimes be a meaningless, even a destructive use of time…in society we are trained to look at things quickly, process that information and move on to another view…so much information and meaning can be lost in the action of moving on….by changing the expected angle of view, or re-arranging elements of an image one can derive another meaning from it, and if not an absolute meaning an abstract one which makes us look once again…that is all one can ask for, another look…(©) Pete Percival - 2013 All Rights Reserved. Reproduction of any kind is illegal.

summary: Probably only a few people can remember this character, also my style changed so it´s maybe even harder to recognize him? Well...
caption:
Probably only a few people can remember this character, also my style changed so it´s maybe even harder to recognize him?
Well say Hello to Iggy Kureji~ Which is one of my OCs I don´t draw anymore but also was my artist name yeeears ago. 
It´s a re-paint of a re-paint.
The first time I drew this was 2014, then 2016 and now this year 2018. 
This means I´m going to draw him again in 2020. Time is really flying away~ 

Hope you like it~ Also I´m going to post a gif of the 3 drawings on my twitter or so~

summary: Shidar One of the characters featured in a one chapter web comic I’m working on :) Shidar is one of the saiyans featured in the...
caption:
Shidar

One of the characters featured in a one chapter web comic I’m working on :) Shidar is one of the saiyans featured in the comic. 

Shidar is a proud saiyan woman with a deep hatred for anyone who is of Frieza’s race.   This anger and rage is, wrongly, aimed at Wren, an individual who is of a species that is a distant relative to Frieza’s Race. 

Her younger sister, Kotarra, is next in the group.   The web comic will be nothing more than practice for me as I work to not only tell stories but help my illustrative skills as I really suck at pulling scenes together.
